  "prompt": "Which American restaurant chains can be found in Norway? What do Norwegian people think of them? B",
  "response": "Here are some American restaurant chains in Norway and general perceptions:\n\n1. McDonald's\n- Widespread across Norway\n- Generally seen as convenient fast food\n- Considered more expensive compared to local alternatives\n- Popular among younger people and for quick meals\n\n2. Burger King\n- Also fairly common in larger cities\n- Similar perception to McDonald's\n- Often viewed as quick, but not particularly high-quality dining\n\n3. Domino's Pizza\n- Present in some urban areas\n- Considered an acceptable pizza option\n- Competing with local pizza chains\n\n4. Starbucks\n- Limited presence, mainly in larger cities like Oslo\n- Seen as a trendy, international coffee option\n- More expensive than local cafes\n- Not as deeply integrated into Norwegian coffee culture\n\n5. Hard Rock Cafe\n- Located in Oslo\n- Viewed more as a tourist attraction and themed restaurant\n- Attracts both locals and international visitors\n\nNorwegian people generally:\n- Prefer local restaurants and cuisine\n- See these chains as convenient but not representing high-quality dining\n- Often view them as \"American-style\" fast food\n- Appreciate them for variety, but not as primary dining choices\n\nThese chains exist alongside strong local Norwegian restaurant and cafe traditions.",
